726341f-a.title: Queens: College Point Park - [Chisholm Mansion.]
726341f-a.text:
College Point Park (Queens): The Chisholm Mansion, built in
1848. Mayor La Guardia used this place in 1937 as his Summer City
Mail.
P. L. Sperr  March 12, 1932
NO REPRODUCTIONS

725024f-a.title: Queens: 14th Avenue - 121st Street
725024f-a.text:
14th Avenue, at the N. W. corner of 121st Street, showing a
private home, erected at the turn of the twentieth century. It
first appears on a 1909 atlas and stands on land formerly be-
longing to Herman Funkel (1873-1891).
P. L. Sperr  March 16, 1932
NO REPRODUCTIONS
